data.title: Ex-Chicago Bull Nazr Mohammed raises money for cancer
data.meta_description: The Nazr Mohammed Foundation is raising money for people affected by cancer through his "Full Court Press Against Cancer."
data.text:
Eighteen-year NBA veteran Nazr Mohammed stopped by WCL to tell us about his latest fundraiser.

The Nazr Mohammed Foundation is raising money for people affected by cancer through his "Full Court Press Against Cancer." Nazr talked about the upcoming fundraiser, and what he's been up to lately.

Full Court Press Against Cancer Fundraiser

Fri., Aug. 5, 2016

Galleria Marchetti

825 W. Erie. Chicago

7:30 p.m. - 10 p.m.

Tickets:

$200 per person for general admission

$300 for VIP (includes meet & greet reception, reserved gaming tables and gift bag)

$150 for the post-party (after 10:00 p.m.)

Tickets can be purchased at www.NazrMohammed.com.

WCL is also giving away two pairs of tickets to the event.
